    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="906"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d906">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.22760H/7–2843</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Assistant Secretary of
                        State</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Berle</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-28">July 28,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Yugoslav Ambassador came in to see me, at his request.</p>
                <p>He mentioned to me a point he had already made to Mr. Cannon.<note n="87"
                        xml:id="d906fn87">Cavendish W. Cannon of the Division of European
                        Affairs.</note> Forty Yugoslav aviators have been in training here to serve
                    in flight units. They finish their training on August 10th. The liaison officer
                    of O.S.S.<note n="88" xml:id="d906fn88">Office of Strategic Services.</note>
                    (Mr. Kimbel) came to the Ambassador with a letter from General Donovan<note
                        n="89" xml:id="d906fn89">William J. Donovan, Director of the Office of
                        Strategic Services.</note> offering commissions in the American Army to
                    these men. The Ambassador said they appreciated the compliment of being offered
                    commissions; but that the whole intent of the arrangement was that these men
                    should serve as a Yugoslav unit, though of course under the American
                    command.</p>
                <p>I said I noted that Mr. Cannon already had the matter in hand, though I would be
                    glad to follow up.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>A[<hi rend="smallcaps">dolf</hi>] A. B[<hi rend="smallcaps">erle</hi>],
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Jr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
